<BaseLayout title="Introduction">
  <h1>Introduction</h1>
  <p>A minimal, dark-accent design system inspired by modern SaaS interfaces like Clerk.com.</p>

  <h2>What is Stoneware?</h2>
  <p>Stoneware is a CSS-first design system that provides everything you need to build clean, professional interfaces. It includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Design Tokens</strong> - CSS custom properties for colors, typography, spacing, shadows, and more</li>
    <li><strong>Component Classes</strong> - Pre-built styles for buttons, inputs, cards, modals, and other UI elements</li>
    <li><strong>Utility Classes</strong> - Helpers for layout, spacing, and common patterns</li>
    <li><strong>Dark Mode</strong> - Full dark mode support via <code>data-theme="dark"</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Design Philosophy</h2>
  <p>Stoneware follows these core principles:</p>

  <h3>Minimal & Clean</h3>
  <p>Remove visual noise. Embrace generous whitespace. Let content breathe.</p>

  <h3>Dark Accents</h3>
  <p>Primary actions use near-black (<code>#18181b</code>), not bright colors. This creates a sophisticated, professional look.</p>

  <h3>Subtle Shadows</h3>
  <p>Light, layered shadows create depth without distraction. Cards feel elevated but not heavy.</p>

  <h3>Smooth Transitions</h3>
  <p>0.15s-0.3s eases for micro-interactions. Fast enough to feel responsive, slow enough to notice.</p>

  <h3>Consistent Spacing</h3>
  <p>4px/8px grid system throughout. Every measurement is intentional.</p>

  <h2>Quick Example</h2>

  <div class="preview">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
